# The Keeper — example environment configuration.
#
# Copy this to .env and fill in real values. The .env file is gitignored.
# This example covers only the variables touched by the URL/API config split;
# the live .env on the Pi also has Discord channel IDs, role IDs, and Google
# Sheets credentials that aren't in scope here.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Discord auth
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TOKEN=                       # bot token from the Discord developer portal
HAVEN_API_KEY=               # Haven extractor API key (issued by Haven super admin)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Haven URL configuration
#
# Three URL variables, three different audiences. Get them right:
#
# HAVEN_API
#   The URL the bot uses to call the Haven backend. On the Pi this is the
#   internal docker network address, because hairpin NAT means the public
#   havenmap.online doesn't resolve back to itself from inside the LAN.
#
# HAVEN_PUBLIC_URL
#   The URL embedded in messages SENT TO Discord — image URLs in embeds,
#   page links, anything Discord's CDN or a user's browser will fetch from
#   the public internet. MUST be the public site URL. Setting this to the
#   internal docker URL produces "Invalid Form Body / Not a well formed URL"
#   400s from Discord (it can't resolve `haven:8005`).
#
# HAVEN_URL
#   Legacy variable used by Haven_stats.py for the "Open the Haven Map" button.
#   Kept as a fallback for HAVEN_PUBLIC_URL so single-host deploys can set
#   just one of them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
HAVEN_API=http://haven:8005
HAVEN_PUBLIC_URL=https://havenmap.online
HAVEN_URL=https://havenmap.online
